China allocated 200 million yuan for disaster relief after a deadly earthquake in Sichuan province claimed over 8,700 lives.
The quake, with a magnitude of 7.8, struck densely populated areas near Chengdu.
Despite no warning signs, Russia's President Medvedev offered condolences and assistance.
The rain forecasted in the region poses challenges to relief efforts.
ASEAN and Vietnam also expressed sympathy and support.
Germany and Norway pledged financial aid, with Belgium offering relief funds.
The State Ethnic Affairs Commission allocated funds to aid ethnic minorities affected by the disaster in Sichuan.
